article.headline: Lipscomb 101, Jacksonville 78
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Senior guard James Poindexter hit 7 of 10 3-pointers and scored a game-high 32 points to lead Lipscomb's 101-78 win over Jacksonville on Saturday. Poindexter also hit 10 of 14 2-point shots and all five of his free throws as Lipscomb (16-8, 12-4 Atlantic Sun) routed Jacksonville (1-23, 1-16 Atlantic Sun). Lipscomb took the lead early and ended the first half leading 51-34. The Bisons shot 50 percent in the second half of the easy win. Brian Fisk scored 20 points for Lipscomb and Shaun Durant and Trey Williams added 10 each. Aubrey Conerly led Jacksonville with 19 points and Evan Jefferson and Mario Brown scored 13 each. Lipscomb hit 57 percent of its shots for the game, while Jacksonville shot 43 percent.
